ake of the case. Edgar struggles rebalancing work and family. Bosch has an unlikely late night visitor.\n |LineColor = FF7F00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 34\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 4\n |Title = Past Lives\n |DirectedBy = [[Tim Hunter (director)|Tim Hunter]]\n |WrittenBy = [[Shaz Bennett]] & Elle Johnson\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|4|13}}\n |ShortSummary = Det. Francis Sheehan comes clean to Bosch, Robertson suspects a leak in the investigation, and Edgar joins the Task Force. Social unrest surrounding the Elias murder grows and Irving is pressured to intervene. Eleanor asks Bosch for parenting advice and confesses the truth about her marriage to Reggie Woo. She is later killed in a ride-by shooting.\n |LineColor = FF7F00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 35\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 5\n |Title = The Coping\n |DirectedBy = Alex Zakrzewski\n |WrittenBy = Jeffrey Fiskin\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|4|13}}\n |ShortSummary = Bosch struggles to manage all the things he's lost and to keep the darkness at bay, from himself, and from Maddie. The Task Force bears down on two suspects. Acting Captain Grace Billets gets tangled in station politics and petty opposition, no longer everyone's best friend.\n |LineColor = FF7F00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 36\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 6\n |Title = The Wine of Youth\n |DirectedBy = [[Zetna Fuentes]]\n |WrittenBy = John Mankiewicz\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|4|13}}\n |ShortSummary = The search for Sheehan intensifies, as pressure mounts to solve the Elias murder. The Task Force waits for ballistics to confirm their suspicions. Edgar and Bosch pursue an unofficial 'side project' in the San Gabriel Valley. Billets and Dets. Crate and Barrel respond to a suspicious hit and run in Hollywood. The Task Force takes Sheehan into custody.\n |LineColor = FF7F00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 37\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 7\n |Title = Missed Connections\n |DirectedBy = [[Daisy von Scherler Mayer]]\n |W