019)===\n{{Episode table |background=#221F54 |overall= |season= |title=25 |director= |writer= |airdate=20 |released=y |country=US |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 41\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Two Kinds of Truth\n |DirectedBy      = [[Alex Zakrzewski]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Daniel Pyne]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|4|19}}\n |ShortSummary    = Detective Harry Bosch learns the DA's office is examining new evidence which threatens to overturn an old case, potentially jeopardizing all of Bosch's other convictions. Meanwhile, a robbery turned murder at a local pharmacy exposes an opioid ring that drags Bosch down a dangerous path.\n |LineColor       = 221F54\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 42\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Pill Shills\n |DirectedBy      = Alex Zakrzewski\n |WrittenBy       = [[Eric Overmyer]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|4|19}}\n |ShortSummary    = Bosch and Edgar uncover more details about the pharmacy murder and the opioid operation, while Detective Robertson works a tandem homicide. As Bosch pushes back against the deathbed confession at the heart of Borders' petition for release, he enlists the help of a longtime adversary. J. Edgar tries to persuade a former CI to cooperate with an investigation.\n |LineColor       = 221F54\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 43\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = The Last Scrip\n |DirectedBy      = [[Daisy von Scherler Mayer]]\n |WrittenBy       = Elle Johnson\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|4|19}}\n |ShortSummary    = Bosch investigates new evidence that may overturn Borders' conviction, but he remains convinced they locked up the right man. Lieutenant Billets is forced to deal with Crate and Barrel's role in the accident at the pharmacy crime scene. Bosch and Edgar track the pill mill van to an unexpected destination, while Edgar gets shocking news about Gary Wise.\n |LineColor       = 221F54\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Epi